==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒbə(r)|-ɒbə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
# Liquid material, generally saliva, that dribbles or [[drool]]s outward and downward from the mouth.
#:''There was dried slobber on his coat lapel.''

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To emit saliva or intaken but not yet swallowed liquid to run from one's mouth. To [[drool]].
#:''All babies slobber.''

